text: Miguelete Creek () is a Uruguayan stream, crossing Montevideo Department. It flows into the Bay of Montevideo and then into the Río de la Plata. It has a very significant history behind, since colonial times. Near its shores are located the big urban park known as Prado and the historical Juan Manuel Blanes Museum. ==See also== *List of rivers of Uruguay ==References== Category:Rivers of Uruguay Category:Rivers of Montevideo Department Category:Prado, Montevideo Category:Capurro
